Scaffold a real-time GPS tracking system called 'Supa-Fleet' using React, Node.js, Tailwind CSS, and Supabase.

Project Structure & Files:

supabase/schema.sql: Write a PostgreSQL script to create a vehicles table with id (UUID), device_id (Text), latitude (Float8), longitude (Float8), status (Text: far/near/immediate), and created_at (TIMESTAMPTZ). Enable Realtime for this table.

server/index.js: Create a lightweight Node.js Express server that acts as a secure API gateway. It should receive POST requests with coordinates, calculate the Haversine distance to a 'Home' coordinate in Kitwe, Zambia (-12.943, 28.639), and upsert the data into Supabase.

client/src/pages/Driver.jsx: A mobile-responsive React page that uses navigator.geolocation.watchPosition to stream live coordinates to the Node.js backend every 5 seconds.

client/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx: A dark-mode 'Command Center' using react-leaflet. It must subscribe to Supabase Realtime 'INSERT' events on the vehicles table.

client/src/hooks/useVoiceAlerts.js: A custom hook that uses window.speechSynthesis to announce when a vehicle's status changes to 'immediate'.

Technical Requirements:

Use the Haversine formula to determine if a device is 'immediate' (< 150m) or 'near' (< 500m) from the home anchor.

In the Dashboard, render a Polyline for each device_id to show its 'breadcrumb' path history.

Ensure the UI is built with Tailwind CSS for a professional look